quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  12,1,Those are the signs of the perspicuous Book
  12,2,"Verily, we have revealed it, an Arabic Qur'an; haply ye may understand"
  12,3,"We tell thee the best of stories, in inspiring thee with this Qur'an, though thou wert before it among the heedless"
  12,4,"When Joseph said to his father, 'O my sire! Verily, I saw eleven stars, and the sun, and the moon,- I saw them adoring me"
  12,5,"He said, 'O my boy! tell not thy vision to thy brethren, for they will plot a plot against thee verily, the devil is to man an open foe"
  12,6,"Thus does thy Lord choose thee, and teach thee the interpretation of sayings, and fulfill His favour upon thee, and upon Jacob's people, as He fulfilled it upon thy two forefathers before thee, Abraham and Isaac,- verily, thy Lord is knowing, wise"